     <body>
     <div type="poem">
   <pb facs="4"/>
   <head>To the Authour, his friend, vpon his Chronicle Historie.</head>
   <l>THese are not to expresse thy <hi>witt,</hi>
   </l>
   <l>But to pronounce thy <hi>Iudgement</hi> fitt;</l>
   <l>In full-fil'd phrase, those Times to rayse,</l>
   <l>When PERKIN ran his wilie wayes.</l>
   <l>Still, let the methode of thy brayne,</l>
   <l>From <hi>Errours</hi> touch, and <hi>Envy's</hi> stayne</l>
   <l>Preserue Thee, free; that eu'r, thy quill</l>
   <l>Fayre <hi>Truth</hi> may wett, and <hi>Fancy</hi> fill.</l>
   <l>Thus <hi>Graces</hi> are, with <hi>Muses</hi> mett,</l>
   <l>And practick <hi>Critick's</hi> on may frett:</l>
   <l>For heere, Thou hast produc't, <hi>A Storie,</hi>
   </l>
   <l>Which shall ecclipfe, <hi>Their</hi> future Glorie.</l>
   <closer>
      <signed>
         <hi>Iohn Brograue:</hi> Ar<gap reason="illegible" resp="#pdcc" extent="1 letter">
            <desc>•</desc>
         </gap>
      </signed>
   </closer>
</div>
